The shape and coloration of thoracic pattern also vary in males; this variation is to some extent geographical: males in the north (for instance from Cuc Phuong, Ba Vi, Xuan Son and Tam Dao National Parks) or from the Central Highlands (e.g. from Kon Ka Kinh National Park) have a U-shaped mark on the mesepisternum formed by a dorsal stripe and a humeral stripe connected anteriorly (
Fig. 11g –i
), but the dorsal stripe is missing and the humeral stripe much truncated in specimens from Ba Na or Bach Ma in central Vietnam ( Fig. 11a ). Males from the north have bluish-green markings when mature (Fig. g–h), but yellowish in males from central Vietnam , for instance from Ba Na, Bach Ma and Kon Ka Kinh ( Fig. 11a, i ).
